WEBVTT

01:34.480 --> 01:37.720
ADAPTED FROM THE NOVEL OF THE SAME NAME
BY ZHU YI ON WWW.JJWXC.NET

01:37.800 --> 01:38.640
SLEEP EARLY, RISE EARLY
SAY NO TO STAYING UP LATE

01:38.720 --> 01:40.640
NANWU UNIVERSITY

01:40.720 --> 01:41.640
You're there?

01:43.720 --> 01:45.920
Qian Fei and the guys
are making hot pot in the dorm tonight.

01:46.520 --> 01:48.880
Anything you want to eat?
I can have them bring you some.

01:51.800 --> 01:53.000
You're not answering,
so I'll take that as "whatever".

01:54.280 --> 01:55.160
Thanks.

02:11.200 --> 02:13.200
Your hometown is in Yihe, right?

02:14.000 --> 02:14.960
Yeah.

02:15.040 --> 02:16.080
Why?

02:16.920 --> 02:19.200
From here, which direction is Yihe?

02:22.120 --> 02:23.560
From the dorm window?

02:24.680 --> 02:25.720
That way, I think.

02:26.480 --> 02:27.320
That way?

02:35.960 --> 02:37.120
YIHE UNIVERSITY

02:37.200 --> 02:39.720
It's been 39 days since I arrived in Yihe.

02:40.520 --> 02:41.520
Autumn has set in.

02:42.600 --> 02:44.600
The nights are cooler.

02:44.680 --> 02:46.360
The sky is often clear.

02:51.880 --> 02:54.360
Is Yihe's autumn as hot as ours?

02:54.440 --> 02:56.000
Pretty much.

02:56.520 --> 02:58.000
But the sky is bluer.

02:58.080 --> 03:00.040
Not like Nanwu, where it's always gray.

03:00.120 --> 03:01.560
No energy in the air.

03:06.040 --> 03:08.280
My roommates are all pretty nice.

03:08.360 --> 03:09.200
Wen Yifan,

03:09.720 --> 03:11.680
I can't sleep with this light on.

03:12.400 --> 03:13.560
Sorry about that.

03:14.360 --> 03:15.280
Thanks.

03:21.400 --> 03:23.560
Why are you suddenly
so interested in Yihe?

03:23.640 --> 03:24.840
I'll take you there next time.

03:30.200 --> 03:31.200
What are you looking at?

03:32.080 --> 03:33.000
Planes.

03:33.840 --> 03:34.680
Look.

03:35.440 --> 03:37.200
There's a streak in the sky.

03:38.560 --> 03:40.040
So sentimental for a science guy.

03:41.120 --> 03:42.800
Maybe you should switch to liberal arts.

03:47.120 --> 03:48.520
Some things…

03:51.320 --> 03:52.600
once they happen,

03:54.680 --> 03:55.840
never really go away.

04:06.320 --> 04:07.640
3,249 DAYS

04:10.720 --> 04:12.000
I get it.

04:12.080 --> 04:14.520
You're saying your friend spent the night

04:14.600 --> 04:16.000
in a guy's arms.

04:16.079 --> 04:18.320
And then that guy had the nerve
to say he was at a loss?

04:18.399 --> 04:19.920
Is your friend really ugly or something?

04:20.440 --> 04:22.040
She's okay-looking.

04:22.120 --> 04:24.680
And that guy
even deliberately walk out shirtless

04:24.760 --> 04:27.400
in front of her after taking a shower?

04:27.920 --> 04:29.680
I just feel like

04:29.760 --> 04:31.160
he probably did it on purpose.

04:31.240 --> 04:33.200
So, I have a serious question.

04:36.240 --> 04:38.600
That guy… Did he react?

04:39.760 --> 04:41.160
Yifan, there you are.

04:43.120 --> 04:44.400
What were you guys talking about?

04:44.480 --> 04:45.440
Nothing.

04:45.520 --> 04:47.320
You showed up at the perfect time.
Since you're young and full of energy,

04:47.400 --> 04:48.760
I have a question for you.

04:49.720 --> 04:51.600
No need to be shy.

04:51.680 --> 04:52.800
It's not even about you.

04:52.880 --> 04:54.800
If a girl were lying next to you,

04:54.880 --> 04:56.400
would you react?

04:57.440 --> 04:58.760
It depends on the girl.

04:58.840 --> 05:00.680
- It depends?
- I'm back!

05:00.760 --> 05:02.080
Here, lady.

05:02.160 --> 05:04.080
- Thanks.
- What's the topic? Let us in on it.

05:04.160 --> 05:06.360
Good timing.

05:06.440 --> 05:08.840
One of Yifan's friends spent the night

05:08.920 --> 05:10.360
in a guy's arms.

05:10.440 --> 05:11.840
They literally just slept?

05:11.920 --> 05:13.560
- Nothing happened?
- Yeah.

05:13.640 --> 05:14.640
Just held each other?

05:14.720 --> 05:16.240
Don't tell me it was Senior Sang Yan.

05:16.760 --> 05:17.680
Yeah…

05:17.760 --> 05:19.520
So, that's what this is about.

05:20.160 --> 05:20.880
It's impossible.

05:20.960 --> 05:23.920
I don't think we should be gossiping
behind people's backs.

05:24.000 --> 05:25.760
Let's drop it.

05:25.840 --> 05:28.520
Do you think he mistook her
for his girlfriend?

05:28.600 --> 05:29.800
Or maybe an ex?

05:29.880 --> 05:31.920
My ex-boyfriend did that to me before.

05:32.000 --> 05:33.440
I think he was just trying to flirt,

05:33.520 --> 05:35.240
but that's such a lame move,

05:35.320 --> 05:36.920
so outdated.

05:37.000 --> 05:38.320
Even I wouldn't stoop that low.

05:38.840 --> 05:42.240
But… I was the one
who climbed into his bed first.

05:42.320 --> 05:43.720
That doesn't make sense.

05:43.800 --> 05:46.880
There was a whole person next to him.
Wouldn't he be scared half to death?

05:46.960 --> 05:48.280
Either he has a girlfriend

05:48.360 --> 05:50.120
and is used to someone being next to him…

05:50.200 --> 05:52.560
Or he did it on purpose. Maybe
he just wanted to take advantage of her.

05:52.640 --> 05:54.640
Or he has some kind of body issue!

05:54.720 --> 05:57.520
That would mean,
not only does he not like her…

05:57.600 --> 05:59.120
- He might actually dislike her!
- Yeah!

05:59.200 --> 06:00.200
But to save face,

06:00.280 --> 06:01.640
he had to act cool

06:01.720 --> 06:03.280
- and act funny.
- Right.

06:29.560 --> 06:31.240
That's all the time
you get to hug me tonight?

06:35.720 --> 06:37.680
You're not exactly that eager…

06:39.640 --> 06:40.760
to get with me.

06:41.680 --> 06:44.360
Even if I can't control my sleepwalking,

06:45.600 --> 06:46.920
with Sang Yan's personality,

06:47.520 --> 06:49.000
if he truly hated it,

06:49.080 --> 06:51.000
he wouldn't put up with it.

06:51.920 --> 06:53.240
He probably would've moved out by now.

06:53.880 --> 06:55.760
But what if…

06:56.280 --> 06:58.680
Have you seen revenge dramas?
They always go like this.

06:59.200 --> 07:01.040
First, he pretends to get close

07:01.640 --> 07:03.880
and acts like he cares about you.
Then, once you're in too deep,

07:03.960 --> 07:05.640
he ruthlessly throws you away.

07:05.720 --> 07:07.120
The perfect revenge.

07:08.080 --> 07:10.440
Could it really be
because I hurt him in the past

07:10.520 --> 07:12.840
and now he's using this to get back at me?

07:14.480 --> 07:17.040
Do you really
have to stare at me like that?

07:18.760 --> 07:19.880
Did I?

07:27.080 --> 07:29.160
Want me to clean your room, too?

07:29.920 --> 07:31.120
No, thanks.

07:31.640 --> 07:32.720
No need to be polite.

07:34.000 --> 07:34.840
Really?

07:47.920 --> 07:48.840
No.

07:49.440 --> 07:50.640
Deep down, I know,

07:51.480 --> 07:52.560
he's not that kind of person.

07:55.640 --> 07:56.560
Here.

07:57.520 --> 07:58.960
Why are you here?

07:59.800 --> 08:00.840
No matter what happens…

08:02.960 --> 08:03.840
I'll always be with you.

08:06.200 --> 08:08.560
He should have anything he wants.

08:09.920 --> 08:13.200
If you have no space to practice dancing,
then just make do here.

08:17.440 --> 08:19.560
He's someone who shines so brightly.

08:23.120 --> 08:24.560
If he…

08:25.800 --> 08:27.320
wants something…

08:28.240 --> 08:29.520
then he should have it.

08:37.760 --> 08:40.039
Even if it's the stars in the sky,

08:43.200 --> 08:45.080
they should be brought down for him.

08:51.120 --> 08:54.200
I never expected
the teacher to call our parents

08:54.280 --> 08:55.880
over this.

08:55.960 --> 08:56.880
Sang Yan…

08:59.720 --> 09:02.120
Can you stop bothering me?

09:02.640 --> 09:03.680
Wen Yifan…

09:05.040 --> 09:06.360
am I really that bad?

09:07.360 --> 09:08.240
I hate it

09:09.000 --> 09:10.800
that every time
I have to come out and see you.

09:12.160 --> 09:13.640
It's frustrating

09:13.720 --> 09:15.240
that you keep coming to Beiyu for me.

09:16.520 --> 09:17.680
So, I chose a place

09:18.280 --> 09:19.640
farther away from Beiyu than Nanwu.

09:21.160 --> 09:22.920
When I go to Yihe,

09:23.000 --> 09:25.400
I hope you won't
come looking for me again.

09:27.760 --> 09:29.240
Sang Yan, you're a great person.

09:30.280 --> 09:31.920
I was the one who hurt you.

09:33.720 --> 09:35.800
Let him stay this way forever,

09:37.320 --> 09:38.200
full of life.

09:42.040 --> 09:43.240
It's better

09:44.440 --> 09:46.240
if we never ran into each other again.

10:16.160 --> 10:17.200
Sang Yan.

10:18.720 --> 10:20.760
- Are you asleep?
- No.

10:22.480 --> 10:23.920
No need to get up and open the door.

10:24.000 --> 10:25.880
I just have a few things to say.

10:29.720 --> 10:31.320
I've thought about it.

10:31.400 --> 10:33.120
Given my current situation,

10:33.640 --> 10:35.600
it's not really suitable for me
to have a roommate.

10:36.800 --> 10:37.800
So…

10:39.720 --> 10:41.320
I'll move out as soon as possible,

10:41.400 --> 10:43.680
find a one-bedroom place, and live alone.

10:44.440 --> 10:45.600
That way, I won't be a bother to you.

10:50.480 --> 10:52.760
I just wanted
to inform you of my decision.

10:53.560 --> 10:56.160
Get some rest.
And don't forget to lock the door.

11:18.240 --> 11:19.400
I don't get it.

11:19.480 --> 11:21.480
You're the one subletting
the place to Sang Yan.

11:21.560 --> 11:23.040
You're technically the landlord.

11:23.120 --> 11:25.400
So, why are you the one
looking for a new place?

11:25.480 --> 11:27.000
Shouldn't he be the one moving out?

11:29.520 --> 11:31.720
He paid several months' rent upfront.

11:31.800 --> 11:33.520
I can't ask him to leave.

11:33.600 --> 11:34.760
Why not?

11:38.680 --> 11:39.960
Because I sleepwalk.

11:41.160 --> 11:43.000
I don't want to bother him.

11:43.080 --> 11:44.880
Sleepwalking is one thing.

11:44.960 --> 11:47.040
But we're talking about first-come,
first-served here.

11:47.640 --> 11:49.800
You were there first.
Why should you be the one to move?

11:51.120 --> 11:53.520
Are you satisfied with this place?

11:53.600 --> 11:54.960
It's okay.

11:55.920 --> 11:58.720
No! It's not going to work.

11:58.800 --> 12:00.880
The kitchen and bedroom
are basically connected.

12:00.960 --> 12:03.800
The cooking fumes will get everywhere.
How am I supposed to sleep?

12:03.880 --> 12:06.200
Also, there are cracks on the walls.

12:06.800 --> 12:08.760
The paint is ugly, too.

12:09.280 --> 12:11.360
I can have someone repaint it for you.

12:11.440 --> 12:13.000
I'm offering with full sincerity.

12:13.520 --> 12:15.440
The rent is already super cheap.

12:15.960 --> 12:18.240
If you like it, just pay a deposit first.

12:18.320 --> 12:19.440
This place is in high demand.

12:19.520 --> 12:21.400
If you hesitate too long,
someone else will take it.

12:21.480 --> 12:24.120
This apartment is so tiny.

12:25.000 --> 12:27.000
And there's a construction site
right outside.

12:27.080 --> 12:29.200
The noise would drive me insane.

12:29.280 --> 12:31.280
It's not worth the original price.

12:31.360 --> 12:32.200
Lower the rent.

12:32.280 --> 12:33.160
That puts me in a tough spot.

12:33.240 --> 12:35.520
In this area,
you won't find a place cheaper than this.

12:35.600 --> 12:37.200
Go ask around if you don't believe me.

12:37.280 --> 12:39.080
If this one won't do, I'll keep looking.

12:39.160 --> 12:40.040
No.

12:41.240 --> 12:43.280
I'll show you my utmost sincerity.
I'll give you a huge discount

12:43.960 --> 12:45.720
on the agency fee. What do you think?

12:45.800 --> 12:47.320
- Sounds good.
- Hey, no.

12:48.040 --> 12:49.520
We appreciate your sincerity,

12:49.600 --> 12:51.440
but we still want to think it over.
Let's check out other options.

12:51.520 --> 12:53.040
- No.
- Thanks.

12:53.120 --> 12:55.520
- Are you happy with it or not?
- We'll keep looking.

12:55.600 --> 12:57.440
The cost-performance ratio
is really high here. Let's discuss it.

12:57.520 --> 12:59.000
We're looking further.

13:01.000 --> 13:02.200
Did you notify Sang Yan?

13:02.280 --> 13:03.440
Notify what?

13:03.960 --> 13:06.960
Don't you two notify each other
if you bring guests home?

13:07.040 --> 13:08.000
It's fine.

13:09.200 --> 13:10.440
You should notify, though.

13:10.520 --> 13:12.760
What if he suddenly comes back?

13:13.600 --> 13:15.960
He's on a business trip today.
He won't be home.

13:16.560 --> 13:17.680
You should've said so earlier.

13:23.400 --> 13:26.000
Why are there so many
pretty little night lights in your place?

13:26.080 --> 13:27.800
And this padding strip?

13:30.880 --> 13:32.280
Sang Yan put them up.

13:34.160 --> 13:37.040
He was worried
you'd hurt yourself sleepwalking.

13:37.120 --> 13:38.520
He's really considerate toward you.

13:38.600 --> 13:39.840
That won't work.

13:40.520 --> 13:43.280
Sleepwalkers don't respond to light.

13:47.320 --> 13:48.640
You two really have no chance?

13:52.040 --> 13:54.160
Forget it. You must have your reasons.

13:54.240 --> 13:56.840
But is just moving out
really the best idea?

13:58.280 --> 14:00.200
At least it'd be better for him.

14:06.880 --> 14:08.160
But yeah,

14:08.240 --> 14:11.760
If you stay, the guilt will only grow.

14:11.840 --> 14:14.320
You see each other every day, after all.

14:15.120 --> 14:18.200
Things from the past you want to forget
aren't so easy to erase.

14:18.280 --> 14:20.080
Maybe moving out is for the best.

14:20.160 --> 14:22.280
You won't dwell on the past anymore.

14:22.960 --> 14:24.040
Go shower.

14:24.720 --> 14:26.880
All right, I'm going.

14:28.680 --> 14:30.560
Think it over.

14:30.640 --> 14:32.320
Why is apartment hunting so exhausting?

14:36.360 --> 14:37.280
Hello?

14:37.360 --> 14:38.280
Miss Wen.

14:39.160 --> 14:40.440
This is Cao from the agency.

14:40.520 --> 14:41.880
Is this a good time to talk?

14:41.960 --> 14:42.880
Yes.

14:43.600 --> 14:47.280
I just wonder if you've made a decision
about today's place.

14:47.800 --> 14:49.120
We're still discussing it.

14:49.200 --> 14:51.720
Could you tell me exactly
what's holding you back?

14:51.800 --> 14:54.280
I can find more options
that suit your needs.

14:58.240 --> 15:00.120
I don't even know
what I'm hesitating about.

15:01.800 --> 15:04.160
All right. Take your time.

15:04.240 --> 15:05.960
But if you do want this place,

15:06.040 --> 15:08.240
make sure to pay the deposit
by tomorrow night.

15:08.320 --> 15:10.440
Otherwise, I'll have to let
another client take it.

15:10.520 --> 15:11.680
Got it.

15:27.960 --> 15:29.080
What are you looking at?

15:30.040 --> 15:31.720
Why is there a white spot here?

15:32.560 --> 15:34.960
After Lin left, that spot's been empty.

15:35.880 --> 15:37.600
I haven't decided what to hang there yet.

15:38.400 --> 15:39.680
I see.

15:39.760 --> 15:42.280
I'll get you a nice painting next time.

15:42.360 --> 15:44.080
Why bother if I'm moving out?

15:45.200 --> 15:47.320
I kept thinking about it in the shower.

15:47.400 --> 15:48.760
Do you really have to move?

15:48.840 --> 15:51.080
Even if you two don't fall
for each other over time

15:51.160 --> 15:52.040
or rekindle old feelings,

15:52.640 --> 15:53.640
he hasn't treated you badly.

15:54.400 --> 15:56.120
I think he's adapted pretty well.

15:56.200 --> 15:58.000
Maybe he even likes your sleepwalking.

15:59.000 --> 16:00.920
Honestly,
he's been giving way to me a lot,

16:01.520 --> 16:03.120
even covering more of the household costs.

16:04.200 --> 16:05.440
Just like this mark on the wall,

16:05.520 --> 16:07.880
a painting was here for so long,
and, of course, it left a trace.

16:09.160 --> 16:12.120
He's holding onto the past.

16:12.640 --> 16:14.320
Some marks deep down

16:14.920 --> 16:15.920
will never fade.

16:17.160 --> 16:19.480
It feels like you're talking about me.

16:19.560 --> 16:20.600
That's why

16:20.680 --> 16:23.240
I went all in haggling
with the agent today.

16:23.320 --> 16:25.400
I want to buy you more time,
so you won't regret it later.

16:26.360 --> 16:27.720
Thank you.

16:27.800 --> 16:29.440
This apartment is great. It's so spacious.

16:29.520 --> 16:31.280
If it were me, I wouldn't move.

16:31.800 --> 16:33.520
Unlike me, I'm already this age

16:33.600 --> 16:36.480
and still living
with my brother and two nieces.

16:37.840 --> 16:40.560
Have you ever considered moving out?

16:41.080 --> 16:42.600
Of course.

16:42.680 --> 16:45.960
But every time I think of my mom,
I change my mind.

16:46.040 --> 16:46.960
Why?

16:47.600 --> 16:48.760
Look,

16:48.840 --> 16:51.480
she wakes up at 5:30 every morning

16:51.560 --> 16:54.520
to make breakfast for the whole family.

16:54.600 --> 16:57.880
Then she spends the day
running the lottery shop.

16:57.960 --> 17:01.120
By the time she gets home to rest,
it's already past midnight.

17:01.640 --> 17:04.040
Her whole life
has been about taking care of others.

17:05.240 --> 17:06.599
If I move out for real,

17:06.680 --> 17:08.760
then all of this work
would be left to her alone.

17:08.839 --> 17:11.839
She must be touched that you stayed.

17:11.920 --> 17:13.480
She has no idea.

17:13.560 --> 17:15.960
She just thinks I'm saving on rent.

17:18.599 --> 17:20.800
You and your mom are the same,

17:21.880 --> 17:23.560
saying one thing but meaning another,

17:23.640 --> 17:25.839
complaining but still living for others.

17:26.680 --> 17:28.359
Isn't that just life?

17:29.080 --> 17:31.320
We're all running around nonstop

17:31.400 --> 17:32.960
just to live for others

17:33.040 --> 17:34.280
and make other people happy.

17:36.280 --> 17:39.440
Why is it that people
are always trying to please others

17:39.520 --> 17:40.800
but forget to be kind to themselves?

17:42.840 --> 17:44.800
Shouldn't we first learn…

17:58.240 --> 18:00.720
Shouldn't we first learn
to love ourselves?

18:32.640 --> 18:33.640
Dian.

18:36.280 --> 18:37.320
Dian.

19:08.560 --> 19:10.840
AUTUMN

19:10.920 --> 19:13.360
Most cases start in childhood.

19:13.440 --> 19:14.640
It gradually improves with age.

19:15.240 --> 19:17.040
But in some cases,

19:17.120 --> 19:18.960
sleepwalking is a late-onset condition.

19:19.040 --> 19:21.600
Though the data is still insufficient.

19:22.320 --> 19:25.240
How has your sleep quality been lately?

19:26.280 --> 19:29.680
When work gets busy, I might sleep less.

19:29.760 --> 19:30.680
Here, sit.

19:32.760 --> 19:35.960
You need to make sure
to maintain regular exercise

19:36.040 --> 19:37.680
and a stable sleep schedule.

19:37.760 --> 19:41.040
When you're sleep-deprived
or under excessive stress,

19:41.120 --> 19:43.200
the chances of sleepwalking increase.

19:43.280 --> 19:45.880
The main trigger is sudden stress.

19:45.960 --> 19:48.080
Have you been under
a lot of pressure lately?

19:48.160 --> 19:49.200
No.

19:49.280 --> 19:51.120
Of course, you have.

19:51.840 --> 19:53.000
Sang Yan.

19:53.520 --> 19:55.040
That doesn't count as stress.

19:55.120 --> 19:55.960
It does.

19:56.680 --> 19:57.880
Do you live alone?

19:58.400 --> 19:59.320
I have a roommate now.

19:59.400 --> 20:01.840
That's good.

20:01.920 --> 20:05.160
At least if anything dangerous happens,
there's someone to keep an eye on you.

20:05.240 --> 20:07.200
Make sure you eat properly

20:07.280 --> 20:08.680
and don't overwork yourself.

20:10.640 --> 20:14.120
Ever since you moved in with Sang Yan,
your sleepwalking got worse.

20:14.200 --> 20:15.280
Didn't it?

20:15.880 --> 20:17.000
Seems like it.

20:17.960 --> 20:20.840
But it's not that frequent.

20:21.760 --> 20:23.280
In total…

20:23.880 --> 20:25.040
five or six times.

20:25.880 --> 20:28.520
So, you're really affected by Sang Yan.
That's a lot of pressure.

20:29.240 --> 20:30.600
He's not pressuring me.

20:31.400 --> 20:33.200
Then, is it work stress?

20:33.880 --> 20:34.960
No.

20:35.960 --> 20:40.240
So, it's neither Sang Yan nor work…

20:40.320 --> 20:42.480
But aren't these
the only two things in your life?

20:42.560 --> 20:43.400
What else is there?

20:44.280 --> 20:45.680
I don't want to see

20:45.760 --> 20:47.640
any of you ever again.

20:47.720 --> 20:49.720
Look, If you like this gentleman…

20:49.800 --> 20:51.800
I'm your mother.

20:51.880 --> 20:53.960
So, my mother can just ignore my feelings?

20:55.040 --> 20:56.040
I have an idea.

20:56.120 --> 20:58.200
If you can't pinpoint the cause,

20:58.280 --> 21:00.680
then just find a way to relieve stress.

21:01.280 --> 21:02.440
How?

21:03.400 --> 21:05.240
Date someone.

21:07.480 --> 21:09.400
If you don't want to develop things
with Sang Yan,

21:09.480 --> 21:11.120
then go find

21:11.200 --> 21:12.960
a new guy.

21:13.560 --> 21:14.520
I can't.

21:15.360 --> 21:16.240
You've never flirted before?

21:17.680 --> 21:19.480
Then what's the point of having this face?

21:19.560 --> 21:21.200
It's such a waste of a good look.

21:23.000 --> 21:25.800
Just be a little more playful
with your words.

21:25.880 --> 21:28.040
When he talks, respond.

21:28.560 --> 21:31.600
But make it seem like you're interested

21:31.680 --> 21:33.440
without being too obvious.

21:33.520 --> 21:35.000
Give me an example.

21:37.520 --> 21:38.600
Start with casual conversation.

21:39.200 --> 21:41.200
Once the topic gets deeper,

21:41.800 --> 21:42.920
ask him about his zodiac sign.

21:43.000 --> 21:46.000
Then, based on that,
praise a few traits of his sign.

21:46.080 --> 21:48.360
For example, I personally like Cancers.

21:48.440 --> 21:50.040
I think they're kind and attentive…

21:50.120 --> 21:52.280
Wouldn't that be too obvious?

21:54.040 --> 21:55.080
No way.

21:56.240 --> 21:58.160
I can't do that.
I've never flirted either.

22:04.720 --> 22:05.560
What is it?

22:05.640 --> 22:07.720
I just saw Su Haoan's grandpa.

22:07.800 --> 22:09.520
- I'll go say hi.
- Alright.

22:09.600 --> 22:11.440
- I'm heading back to the TV station.
- Okay, bye.

22:11.520 --> 22:13.040
- Say hi to Grandpa for me.
- Will do.

22:21.960 --> 22:22.800
Grandpa.

22:23.320 --> 22:25.520
- What are you doing here?
- Hello.

22:28.040 --> 22:29.560
Grandpa.

22:29.640 --> 22:31.120
Are you here to see a doctor?

22:31.200 --> 22:32.280
Which department?

22:33.040 --> 22:34.000
Oh, right.

22:34.520 --> 22:36.240
Which department am I here for?

22:37.800 --> 22:39.120
Grandpa, if you haven't finished
your check-up,

22:39.200 --> 22:40.400
how about I stay with you?

22:41.280 --> 22:45.200
Okay. But which department am I seeing?

22:46.280 --> 22:47.280
Where's Uncle Ma?

22:48.280 --> 22:51.200
- Right, where's Ma?
- Sir!

22:52.200 --> 22:54.720
Ma, where did you go?

22:54.800 --> 22:55.640
Sir,

22:55.720 --> 22:58.560
I should be asking you that.
Where did you go?

22:58.640 --> 23:00.440
I parked the car.

23:00.520 --> 23:01.840
And when I went to the entrance,

23:01.920 --> 23:03.360
you were gone.

23:03.440 --> 23:06.160
This hospital is too big.
It's easy for Grandpa to get lost.

23:06.240 --> 23:07.840
It's okay. I'll stay with you.

23:08.560 --> 23:10.480
No need. Thank you.

23:10.560 --> 23:11.880
It's fine. No need to be so polite.

23:11.960 --> 23:14.520
Let's go see the doctor now.

23:14.600 --> 23:15.920
See you later.

23:16.000 --> 23:17.360
Bye, Qiao.

23:19.480 --> 23:23.560
NEUROLOGY DEPARTMENT

23:33.080 --> 23:34.400
Dr. Liu.

23:34.480 --> 23:35.600
Have a seat.

23:37.960 --> 23:40.720
Dr. Liu, truly sorry.

23:41.280 --> 23:43.400
I just found the patient.

23:43.480 --> 23:45.480
He got lost earlier.

23:45.560 --> 23:47.560
Next time,
it's best to have a family member

23:47.640 --> 23:48.760
come with you.

23:48.840 --> 23:50.800
I need to speak with them.

23:51.880 --> 23:54.280
Ma is with me. He is my family.

23:55.360 --> 23:57.480
I meant your wife and grandson.

23:58.080 --> 24:00.600
Didn't you say last time
that they're still around?

24:00.680 --> 24:03.200
Do they know about your condition?

24:03.280 --> 24:05.600
They know.

24:10.480 --> 24:11.760
Hello? Su Haoan.

24:11.840 --> 24:13.480
You won't believe this.

24:13.560 --> 24:15.480
I just ran into Grandpa at the hospital.

24:15.560 --> 24:16.720
I know.

24:16.800 --> 24:18.360
Uncle Ma told me.

24:18.440 --> 24:20.640
Do you know about Grandpa's health?

24:20.720 --> 24:21.760
Of course I do.

24:21.840 --> 24:23.000
Isn't it just a diabetes follow-up?

24:23.760 --> 24:25.840
He's seeing a neurologist.

24:28.600 --> 24:30.240
Grandpa, you're back?

24:39.960 --> 24:41.200
Grandpa?

24:43.760 --> 24:44.760
Grandpa?

24:45.840 --> 24:46.680
Grandpa?

24:49.920 --> 24:51.000
Grandpa?

25:05.600 --> 25:08.320
Mr. Su's cognitive decline
is progressing faster.

25:09.000 --> 25:11.440
He is now in the early stages of dementia.

25:15.480 --> 25:16.360
Then…

25:17.560 --> 25:18.440
Can this disease be cured?

25:19.200 --> 25:22.120
Completely reversing it is impossible.

25:22.200 --> 25:24.120
But with timely treatment
and intervention,

25:24.200 --> 25:27.000
we can slow down its progression.

25:27.080 --> 25:28.920
What you should focus on now

25:29.000 --> 25:31.240
is how to support his treatment

25:31.320 --> 25:34.120
and how to take care of him in the future.

25:34.200 --> 25:37.760
Alzheimer's
doesn't just challenge the patient.

25:37.840 --> 25:38.960
It challenges the family as well.

25:40.960 --> 25:42.800
The symptoms were already there.

25:42.880 --> 25:44.120
What was I even doing?

25:44.640 --> 25:45.960
Don't blame yourself.

25:46.040 --> 25:48.080
Didn't the doctor say

25:48.160 --> 25:50.360
the early stage
is just mild forgetfulness?

25:50.440 --> 25:52.840
Even young people
forget things all the time.

25:52.920 --> 25:54.680
It's really hard to notice.

25:54.760 --> 25:57.320
And every case is different.

25:57.400 --> 25:59.440
I've seen Grandpa so many times.

25:59.520 --> 26:01.880
I still can't believe he has Alzheimer's.

26:01.960 --> 26:03.120
What do we do now?

26:04.320 --> 26:06.280
What do I need to prepare? I have no clue.

26:06.360 --> 26:07.680
Don't worry.

26:07.760 --> 26:09.880
I know an old lady
who treats me like her own granddaughter.

26:09.960 --> 26:11.680
And she's one of my long-time clients.

26:11.760 --> 26:13.960
She has been taking care
of her husband with Alzheimer's

26:14.040 --> 26:14.880
for over a decade.

26:15.480 --> 26:17.160
We can ask her for advice.

26:20.800 --> 26:21.880
Thanks.

26:22.400 --> 26:23.880
I'll go talk to Grandpa now

26:23.960 --> 26:25.120
that I already know everything.

26:25.200 --> 26:26.040
See how things go.

26:31.680 --> 26:33.000
Grandpa?

26:34.760 --> 26:35.800
Grandpa?

26:37.960 --> 26:39.000
Grandpa?

26:40.800 --> 26:41.960
He's probably not home.

26:44.600 --> 26:46.840
Uncle Ma. Where's my grandpa?

26:49.800 --> 26:50.720
Woodie…

26:51.840 --> 26:53.520
passed away this morning.

27:16.840 --> 27:18.440
Give Grandpa some time.

27:26.040 --> 27:27.760
I may have picked up Woodie,

27:28.920 --> 27:31.480
but Grandpa spent 16 years with him.

27:32.520 --> 27:33.800
Aside from Grandma,

27:35.160 --> 27:37.440
Woodie was probably
Grandpa's closest companion.

28:18.480 --> 28:20.320
Everyone's on break
for the National Holiday,

28:20.400 --> 28:21.400
and you're still working?

28:22.560 --> 28:23.920
Aren't you on duty, too?

28:24.000 --> 28:27.400
We work in news. There are always
big stories during the holidays.

28:29.600 --> 28:30.920
But…

28:31.000 --> 28:32.800
I get a week off after Golden Week.

28:32.880 --> 28:34.800
Then I'll take leave, too.
Let's go have some fun.

28:35.480 --> 28:37.200
You're talking like you're my boyfriend.

28:37.840 --> 28:38.760
Aren't I?

28:39.920 --> 28:41.320
I like men.

28:44.280 --> 28:45.720
How are things with Sang Yan?

28:47.000 --> 28:48.720
We've both been super busy.

28:48.800 --> 28:51.400
We barely even see each other at home.

28:52.080 --> 28:53.200
What about the moving situation?

28:53.720 --> 28:54.800
We haven't had a chance to talk.

28:55.720 --> 28:58.280
And I've brought it up so many times,

28:58.360 --> 28:59.960
but he doesn't seem to care.

29:03.000 --> 29:03.920
Why are you laughing?

29:04.440 --> 29:06.400
He's been crazy busy lately.

29:06.480 --> 29:07.440
Su Haoan told me

29:07.520 --> 29:09.600
his family has been setting him up
on blind dates.

29:10.240 --> 29:11.520
Blind dates?

29:11.600 --> 29:12.960
Yeah, he's been to several already.

29:13.040 --> 29:14.280
It's kind of funny.

29:14.360 --> 29:16.760
With his options,
does he even need blind dates?

29:17.440 --> 29:18.280
Right.

29:18.880 --> 29:21.560
I guess,
since you're not rekindling anything,

29:21.640 --> 29:22.520
he's in a hurry to find someone.

29:26.040 --> 29:28.680
UPTOWN FLOWER CITY

29:30.720 --> 29:32.840
I unconsciously ordered for two again.

29:33.960 --> 29:35.200
What now?

29:36.120 --> 29:37.280
You want some?

29:42.520 --> 29:45.160
I thought you wouldn't be back
until tomorrow from your business trip.

29:46.040 --> 29:47.760
The work was simple.
I finished early and came back.

29:51.120 --> 29:52.400
I ordered takeout.

29:53.080 --> 29:55.040
I ordered too much. Want to share?

29:55.120 --> 29:56.800
PIZZA HUT

29:58.360 --> 29:59.400
I bought soup for myself.

30:21.000 --> 30:22.480
You didn't drink my porridge,

30:23.200 --> 30:24.640
but you want me to share your pizza?

30:25.400 --> 30:27.280
I made porridge. Help me finish it.

30:29.040 --> 30:29.920
It's fine.

30:30.000 --> 30:31.040
I'll just have cereal.

30:33.720 --> 30:35.120
You really hold grudges.

30:37.280 --> 30:39.880
I will… I'll eat it next time.

30:52.720 --> 30:54.120
Ask him his zodiac sign.

30:54.200 --> 30:57.120
Then mention something good about it.

31:01.280 --> 31:02.800
I heard…

31:03.640 --> 31:07.000
Capricorn men are super gentle
and very responsible…

31:07.080 --> 31:09.280
What did the doctor say
about your sleepwalking?

31:13.320 --> 31:14.640
The doctor told me

31:15.160 --> 31:16.480
to keep a regular schedule

31:16.560 --> 31:17.680
and manage stress.

31:17.760 --> 31:19.200
Having a roommate

31:19.280 --> 31:20.680
is the best.

31:22.320 --> 31:25.000
So, basically… you need me?

31:26.920 --> 31:29.280
The doctor said
if I don't have a roommate,

31:29.360 --> 31:30.600
I have to be extra careful.

31:39.240 --> 31:40.360
So, are you still moving?

31:41.120 --> 31:42.920
If I'm not bothering you…

31:48.720 --> 31:50.120
Do you want to move?

31:55.400 --> 31:56.600
Honestly…

31:59.480 --> 32:00.760
Not really.

32:10.400 --> 32:12.240
Capricorn men

32:12.320 --> 32:13.280
are indeed quite outstanding.

32:14.000 --> 32:15.400
Your research is correct.

32:23.640 --> 32:25.280
I'll heat up your soup.

32:33.280 --> 32:34.120
Hello?

32:34.200 --> 32:35.680
Miss Wen, this is Cao.

32:36.920 --> 32:38.560
I found four more places
that match your criteria.

32:38.640 --> 32:41.320
Check your WeChat.
I can arrange a viewing.

32:42.160 --> 32:43.160
Sorry.

32:43.240 --> 32:44.720
No need to call me anymore.

32:44.800 --> 32:46.480
I don't need to rent a place now.

32:54.240 --> 32:56.920
UPTOWN FLOWER CITY

33:08.720 --> 33:09.800
Is this Yan's place?

33:10.560 --> 33:11.400
Yes.

33:13.400 --> 33:15.040
I'm his mother. Is he home?

33:15.120 --> 33:16.280
Auntie, please come in.

33:19.440 --> 33:20.360
Yan.

33:21.280 --> 33:23.640
Mom. What brings you here?

33:24.800 --> 33:25.960
I brought Kexin with me.

33:27.560 --> 33:29.360
You two sit first.
I'm grabbing the laundry.

33:34.880 --> 33:37.360
Auntie, is this your first time
visiting Yan's place too?

33:38.720 --> 33:39.760
Yes.

33:40.840 --> 33:43.600
Auntie, I hope I'm not intruding today.

33:43.680 --> 33:44.800
Would Yan…

33:44.880 --> 33:45.760
No worries.

33:45.840 --> 33:47.240
What does Yan like to eat?

33:48.320 --> 33:50.360
We'll take him out
for something nice later.

33:50.440 --> 33:51.280
Sounds good.

33:52.280 --> 33:53.120
Thank you.

33:53.200 --> 33:54.160
- Auntie, here.
- Alright.

33:54.240 --> 33:56.280
- Thanks.
- Take your time chatting.

33:58.720 --> 34:00.080
Auntie, have some water.

34:00.160 --> 34:01.440
You drink it.

34:03.040 --> 34:05.440
- Kexin, stay here.
- Okay.

34:10.320 --> 34:12.040
What are you busy with?

34:13.679 --> 34:14.840
I'm heating up food, Auntie.

34:16.600 --> 34:18.400
Have we met before?

34:18.480 --> 34:20.639
You look really familiar.

34:21.199 --> 34:23.719
Yes, we have, back in high school.

34:24.360 --> 34:26.000
You kids are under
so much academic pressure.

34:26.080 --> 34:27.600
Dating too early
would just be a distraction.

34:27.679 --> 34:29.040
Do you really like her?

34:30.600 --> 34:31.840
If you do, then hold on.

34:31.920 --> 34:33.320
Wait until college.

34:37.679 --> 34:41.400
You're the girl
who dated Yan in high school?

34:41.480 --> 34:42.960
We weren't dating back then.

34:44.960 --> 34:47.760
Let me tell you,
Yan has always been a rebellious kid.

34:47.840 --> 34:49.840
He gave us plenty of headaches.

34:49.920 --> 34:52.400
Since elementary school,
his grades were just average.

34:52.480 --> 34:54.040
We pretty much gave up on him.

34:54.120 --> 34:57.520
But then, out of nowhere,
he started working insanely hard.

34:57.600 --> 34:59.960
And now… you're his new roommate.

35:02.440 --> 35:03.280
Are you free tomorrow?

35:04.080 --> 35:06.520
We can go watch a movie together.

35:06.600 --> 35:09.120
Yan has been out of college for years

35:09.200 --> 35:10.960
and still hasn't had a girlfriend.

35:11.040 --> 35:12.920
It worried us so much.

35:13.000 --> 35:13.960
We even wondered

35:14.040 --> 35:15.800
if it was because we didn't
let him date back then.

35:15.880 --> 35:17.840
Why are you doing your own laundry?

35:21.400 --> 35:22.360
Mom.

35:23.040 --> 35:25.320
Auntie, you guys keep talking.
I'll head back to my room.

35:25.400 --> 35:26.680
Okay.

35:30.520 --> 35:32.520
Did that little brat spill the beans?

35:32.600 --> 35:36.480
Sang Yan, you're living with her, a lady.

35:36.560 --> 35:37.520
Did you tell Mom and Dad?

35:38.640 --> 35:40.320
You've been off the radar for so long.

35:40.400 --> 35:41.520
Of course, I had to check in.

35:42.120 --> 35:44.120
Didn't I go on a business trip recently?

35:47.600 --> 35:48.440
Kexin.

35:48.520 --> 35:50.400
- Auntie.
- Stay a little longer.

35:50.480 --> 35:52.040
I need to talk to Yan.

35:52.120 --> 35:53.680
- Okay.
- Just stay for a bit.

36:13.600 --> 36:15.320
What's wrong with you?

36:16.480 --> 36:19.120
Last time, you were set up with Miss Yu.
And then you just disappeared.

36:19.200 --> 36:21.200
Her mother had to come looking for me,

36:21.280 --> 36:23.880
and that's when I found out you two
never even kept in touch.

36:29.840 --> 36:31.680
Tell me the truth.

36:31.760 --> 36:32.960
You don't like her, do you?

36:33.040 --> 36:34.280
Do you have someone else in mind?

36:39.320 --> 36:41.200
Is it that girl who opened the door?

36:41.280 --> 36:42.760
Is she your girlfriend?

36:43.360 --> 36:45.280
Is she your girlfriend? If she is…

36:45.360 --> 36:46.680
Why is Auntie suddenly so excited?

36:46.760 --> 36:48.720
I won't have to set you up
on blind dates anymore.

36:53.080 --> 36:56.040
For now… she's not.

36:56.720 --> 36:58.320
Then, do you like her?

37:01.160 --> 37:02.680
You brat.

37:02.760 --> 37:04.440
If you do, go after her.

37:05.280 --> 37:07.920
- You're a man.
- Does Sang Yan like that girl?

37:08.480 --> 37:11.080
All right.
You don't need to worry about me.

37:11.160 --> 37:13.160
Then, who else would I worry about?

37:13.240 --> 37:14.400
Honestly.

37:14.480 --> 37:15.560
Sounds like

37:15.640 --> 37:17.920
Sang Yan really does
have feelings for her.

37:18.000 --> 37:19.040
Treat us to a meal, then.

37:19.120 --> 37:20.840
No nonsense. Hurry up.

37:20.920 --> 37:22.680
Come on. Go change.

37:24.160 --> 37:25.120
Get ready.

37:25.200 --> 37:26.560
Something's burning.

37:27.280 --> 37:28.800
She's so careless.

37:28.880 --> 37:29.920
You two live together.

37:30.000 --> 37:31.640
If there's a fire, it'll be a disaster.

37:32.400 --> 37:33.680
Turn it off, quick.

37:35.080 --> 37:37.640
Kexin, let's go eat out later.
What do you want to eat?

37:37.720 --> 37:39.080
Anything's fine, Auntie.

37:39.160 --> 37:40.720
I'll go with whatever Sang Yan wants.

38:06.920 --> 38:08.120
Have you eaten?

38:10.480 --> 38:11.760
Eat with me.

38:12.360 --> 38:13.480
You haven't eaten yet?

38:14.320 --> 38:15.320
Not yet.

38:22.480 --> 38:23.520
You're not eating?

38:24.680 --> 38:26.200
You go ahead. I'll take a shower first.

38:38.320 --> 38:39.840
I reheated it.

38:40.440 --> 38:42.360
Let's eat together later.

38:48.240 --> 38:50.160
Didn't you say you'd shower first?

38:51.720 --> 38:53.520
Food is best eaten while it's hot.

39:01.560 --> 39:03.720
I wonder how his date went.

39:04.520 --> 39:07.120
I know this might be a bit hard for you
to accept right now…

39:08.760 --> 39:10.000
but please believe me.

39:11.520 --> 39:14.040
I'm the one who suits you best.

39:20.040 --> 39:21.520
What's wrong? You're not hungry?

39:26.120 --> 39:27.880
Or do you want to ask

39:27.960 --> 39:28.960
if my date went well?

39:30.440 --> 39:31.680
No.

39:38.200 --> 39:39.480
I just wanted to say

39:40.000 --> 39:41.600
you've been dressing

39:41.680 --> 39:44.200
a bit too revealing lately
in the common areas.

39:45.760 --> 39:47.760
It's just normal clothes.
No inappropriate intent.

39:49.720 --> 39:50.960
Are you afraid you can't control yourself?

39:51.680 --> 39:52.600
I…

39:53.280 --> 39:54.840
- I think it's fine.
- Can't you just control yourself?

39:57.280 --> 39:58.240
I know.

39:58.320 --> 40:00.440
I have a face that makes people
want to commit crimes.

40:01.720 --> 40:03.400
But we're all adults.

40:06.520 --> 40:07.960
Can't you have a little self-restraint?

40:08.040 --> 40:10.040
When he talks, you have to respond.

40:10.120 --> 40:11.400
But don't be too obvious.

40:11.480 --> 40:12.640
Keep it flirty.

40:17.240 --> 40:18.160
I can't.

40:20.160 --> 40:21.560
I'm afraid I might commit a crime.

40:21.640 --> 40:22.680
Oh my gosh.

40:22.760 --> 40:23.840
What did I just say?

40:24.560 --> 40:25.400
How is this flirty?

40:26.680 --> 40:28.880
No. I just mean

40:28.960 --> 40:30.960
you should be more mindful.

40:33.400 --> 40:34.320
Wait.

40:35.720 --> 40:36.720
Tell me.

40:37.320 --> 40:39.320
What crime are you afraid you'll commit?

40:42.640 --> 40:43.880
Just…

40:46.360 --> 40:47.480
I was just responding to you.

40:50.280 --> 40:51.520
You want to vio (qin)…

40:52.600 --> 40:53.560
Kiss (qin)…

40:54.280 --> 40:55.600
Violate me?

41:18.200 --> 41:19.400
If you dare, go ahead.

41:22.720 --> 41:24.200
That's not what I meant.

41:25.440 --> 41:26.680
So, you don't dare, huh?

41:38.000 --> 41:39.080
Star Sang,

41:39.600 --> 41:41.040
as expected, is always number one.

41:42.240 --> 41:44.000
But why would I need to dare?

42:10.600 --> 42:12.320
So, you're a Capricorn.

42:14.640 --> 42:15.840
It's an earth sign.

42:16.360 --> 42:18.480
I have a few Capricorn friends.

42:18.560 --> 42:20.720
They all have great personalities.

42:20.800 --> 42:22.800
But when they get stubborn,

42:22.880 --> 42:23.720
no one can beat them.

42:23.800 --> 42:26.880
That kind of contrast
makes Capricorns really cute.

42:27.400 --> 42:28.640
I actually really like Capricorns.

42:34.000 --> 42:34.960
And…

42:35.640 --> 42:38.600
And Capricorns love making friends.

42:38.680 --> 42:40.440
But I'm naturally quiet.

42:44.280 --> 42:46.280
The restroom is packed.

42:47.080 --> 42:48.240
I'm heading out.

42:49.000 --> 42:50.680
- Sir, here's your order.
- Thanks.

42:50.760 --> 42:53.040
Yan. What's up with you?

42:53.120 --> 42:54.800
Didn't you say
you were treating us to dinner?

42:54.880 --> 42:56.760
The food is served. I even paid the bill.

42:56.840 --> 42:58.800
But… you haven't even eaten.

42:58.880 --> 43:00.600
Treating someone to a meal doesn't mean
I have to eat with them.

43:01.600 --> 43:05.000
- Enjoy your meal.
- Yan. Yan.

43:05.720 --> 43:06.760
Honestly.

45:53.240 --> 45:54.280
HUGE THANKS TO EVERYONE INVOLVED
AND TO ALL THE FANS OF THE FIRST FROST!

45:54.360 --> 45:55.520
TREAT YOURSELF WELL
AND THE WORLD WILL HOLD MORE LOVE FOR YOU!
